Description: Use XDG directories for user data, screenshots and printer output
 Apply the XDG Base Directory specification to default paths:
 .
  * snap_path, cart_path, dsk_path, tape_path
    default to $XDG_DATA_HOME/caprice32/<subdir>
    (i.e. $HOME/.local/share/caprice32/snap etc.)
 .
  * sdump_dir (screenshots)
    default to $XDG_PICTURES_DIR as read from
    ~/.config/user-dirs.dirs (localised: "Images" on French systems),
    falling back to $HOME/Pictures.
 .
  * printer_file
    default to $XDG_DOCUMENTS_DIR/printer.dat,
    falling back to $HOME/Documents/printer.dat.
 .
 All these defaults are used only when the corresponding key is absent
 or empty in cap32.cfg; an explicit value in the config is always
 respected.  The four data directories are created on startup if needed.
 .
 cap32.cfg.tmpl is updated to ship empty values for all five entries so
 the installed /etc/cap32.cfg no longer contains hard-coded system paths.
